<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-07-26T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-07-26T16:00:00-05:00" n="640" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d640">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A4e/625: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-07-26T17:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">July 26,
                                        1926—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>148. Your 298, July 24, 3 p.m. [<hi rend="italic">a.m.</hi>], 301, July
                            24, 6 p.m. Department approves action taken by you, as stated
                            therein.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
